We can look at the definition of `NullMeasurableSet`:

```tactics
structure NullMeasurableSet (s : Set ℝ) (μ : Measure ℝ) : Prop where
  exists : ∃ t, t ∈ σμ ∧ t =ᶠ[μ] s
```

So `h` gives us a measurable set `t` such that `t` is almost equal to `s`. The definition of `almost equal` (`=ᶠ[μ]`) is that the symmetric difference has measure zero.

